pectations surrounding the strong link between an individual author subject and its alienable text, a link that several postmodern writers powerfully question and violate. Identifying three distinct practices of postmodern plagiarism, the book examines their specific situatedness, precepts, and subversive potential as litmus tests for the literary market, and the ongoing dynamic notion of the concepts authorship, originality, and creativity.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 4aAuthorship. 4aAutorschaft. 4aGeistiges Eigentum. 4aIntellectual Property. 4aLiterarischer Markt. 4aLiterary Market. 4aPlagiarism. 4aPlagiat. 4aPostmodern Literature. 4aSubversion. 70(DE-601)1041809350(DE-588)4046196-8aPlagiat2gnd 70(DE-601)1042885150(DE-588)4115604-3aPostmoderne2gnd 70(DE-601)1047441380(DE-588)4053309-8aSchriftsteller2gnd 70(DE-601)1062450150(DE-588)4035964-5aLiteratur2gnd 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2015z9783110438673oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831103942690 cprintz978311037895540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110379105423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110379105.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DKUb2015